@startuml
skinparam classAttributeIconSize 0

title "Patrón Template Method\nVistas Basadas en Clases (CBV) de Django"

abstract class View {
  + dispatch(request, *args, **kwargs)
  #{abstract} get(request, *args, **kwargs)
  #{abstract} post(request, *args, **kwargs)
}

abstract class TemplateView {
  - template_name: String
  + get(request, *args, **kwargs)
  #{abstract} get_context_data(**kwargs)
}

abstract class FormView {
  - form_class: Form
  - template_name: String
  - success_url: String
  + get(request, *args, **kwargs)
  + post(request, *args, **kwargs)
  #{abstract} form_valid(form)
  #{abstract} form_invalid(form)
}

class "VistaRegistro\n(UserRegisterForm)" as RegView {
  + get(request)
  + post(request)
  - form_valid(form)
  - form_invalid(form)
}

class "LoginView" as LogView {
  + get(request)
  + post(request)
  - form_valid(form)
  - form_invalid(form)
}

View <|-- TemplateView
View <|-- FormView

TemplateView <|-- "LandingView\n(TemplateView)" : "plantilla fija"
FormView <|-- RegView : "registro"
FormView <|-- LogView : "login"

note top of View : Template Method\ndispatch() define el\nesqueleto del algoritmo\n-> get() o post() según HTTP

note bottom of RegView : El formulario inválido\ndevuelve errores al usuario\nEl formulario válido\nredirige al login

@enduml
